libbc-allocators (1.2.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * feat(arena): growable arena via linked chunk chain. New API
    `bc_allocators_arena_create_growable(ctx, initial_chunk_size,
    max_chunk_size, out)` creates an arena that grows geometrically
    (2x per new chunk, capped at max_chunk_size; 0 = uncapped).
    Pointers returned by allocate() remain stable for the lifetime
    of the arena — chunks are linked, never relocated.
  * `bc_allocators_arena_create()` behavior preserved: fixed
    capacity, no growth (growable=false). Backwards-compatible.
  * `bc_allocators_arena_reset()` now drops extra chunks and keeps
    only the first, ready for reuse. `reset_secure` and
    `release_pages` walk all chunks.
  * `bc_allocators_arena_stats_t` extended with `chunk_count` and
    `total_reserved` (appended at end of struct, ABI-compatible).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Wed, 22 Apr 2026 22:00:00 +0100

libbc-allocators (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * feat(typed_array): add `prefix_append_bulk(mem, arr, src, count)` to
    BC_TYPED_ARRAY_DEFINE, generating a memcpy-based bulk append method.
    Used by bc-seek to drop a 110-line custom byte_buffer implementation.
  * No ABI change (macro-based; all generated symbols remain static
    inline). Consumers of existing push/reserve/clear/destroy are
    unaffected.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 21:30:00 +0000

libbc-allocators (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial public release.
  * Pool allocator: general-purpose allocate / reallocate / free
    with a 1 GB default capacity.
  * Arena allocator: bump-pointer with bulk reset, secure-wipe,
    page-release, and string copy helpers.
  * Slab allocator: fixed-size O(1) alloc / free for hot object pools.
  * Context: threads leak-warning callbacks and statistics.
  * Typed array: growable primitive absorbed from bc-containers.
  * Full sanitizer coverage (asan / tsan / ubsan / memcheck) and
    cppcheck-clean sources.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000
